text: Biryuchek () is a rural locality (a selo) in Semibugrinsky Selsoviet, Kamyzyaksky District, Astrakhan Oblast, Russia. The population was 552 as of 2010. There are 5 streets. == Geography == It is located on the Chyornaya River. == References == Category:Rural localities in Kamyzyaksky District
title: Biryuchek
